data.title: CBI Oral Histories
data.text:
CBI holds one of the world's largest collections of research-grade oral history interviews relating to the history of computers, software, and networking. The Collection contains over 550 oral history interviews in both print (only available onsite at CBI) and digital. Learn more about CBI's Oral History Program

Popular Search Topics

CBI holds an extensive number of of electronic transcripts. Many researchers utilize the Collections for topics related to Women's History, Gender, ARPANET, Control Data and GE. We have created a few quick links to our most popular topics.
